text: Managora () is a rural locality (a selo) in Lemezinsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 46 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 73 km from Iglino, 8 km from Nizhniye Lemezy. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Managora
